# Adding an Application

Step-by-step guide to onboard a new application to this GitOps repository.

{{- if eq (printf "%s" .ManifestType) "helm"}}

## 1. Create the Helm chart

Create a directory under `environments/base/` with your application name:

```
environments/base/<app-name>/
├── Chart.yaml
├── values.yaml
└── templates/
    ├── _helpers.tpl
    ├── deployment.yaml
    └── service.yaml
```

**Chart.yaml:**

```yaml
apiVersion: v2
name: <app-name>
description: Helm chart for <app-name>
type: application
version: 0.1.0
appVersion: "latest"
```

**values.yaml** — default values for replicas, image, ports, resources, and probes.

## 2. Create per-environment values

For each environment, create a values file:

```
{{- range .Environments}}
environments/{{.Name}}/<app-name>/values.yaml
{{- end}}
```

Override environment-specific values (replicas, resources, image tags):

```yaml
replicaCount: 3

image:
  tag: "v1.2.3"
```

{{- if eq (printf "%s" .Controller.Type) "argocd"}}
## 3. Create ArgoCD Application definitions

For each environment, create an Application YAML in `apps/`:

```
{{- range .Environments}}
apps/<app-name>-{{.Name}}.yaml
{{- end}}
```

Each Application points to the chart with environment-specific values:

```yaml
apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1
kind: Application
metadata:
  name: <app-name>-<environment>
  namespace: argocd
  finalizers:
    - resources-finalizer.argocd.argoproj.io
spec:
  project: default
  source:
    repoURL: <this-repo-url>
    targetRevision: HEAD
    path: environments/base/<app-name>
    helm:
      releaseName: <app-name>
      valueFiles:
        - ../../environments/<environment>/<app-name>/values.yaml
  destination:
    server: https://kubernetes.default.svc
    namespace: <environment>
  syncPolicy:
    syncOptions:
      - CreateNamespace=true
```
{{- else}}
## 3. Create Flux HelmRelease definitions

For each environment, create a HelmRelease YAML in `apps/`:

```
{{- range .Environments}}
apps/<app-name>-{{.Name}}.yaml
{{- end}}
```

Each HelmRelease points to the chart with environment-specific values:

```yaml
apiVersion: helm.toolkit.fluxcd.io/v2
kind: HelmRelease
metadata:
  name: <app-name>-<environment>
  namespace: flux-system
spec:
  interval: 5m0s
  releaseName: <app-name>
  targetNamespace: <environment>
  chart:
    spec:
      chart: ./environments/base/<app-name>
      sourceRef:
        kind: GitRepository
        name: gitops-repo
        namespace: flux-system
  values:
    replicaCount: <replica-count>
```
{{- end}}

{{- else}}

## 1. Create the base manifests

Create a directory under `environments/base/` with your application name:

```
environments/base/<app-name>/
├── kustomization.yaml
├── deployment.yaml
└── service.yaml
```

**kustomization.yaml:**

```yaml
apiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1
kind: Kustomization

resources:
  - deployment.yaml
  - service.yaml
```

**deployment.yaml** — adjust image, port, resources, and probes to match your application.

**service.yaml** — expose the appropriate port.

## 2. Create environment overlays

For each environment, create an overlay directory:

```
{{- range .Environments}}
environments/{{.Name}}/<app-name>/kustomization.yaml
{{- end}}
```

Each overlay references the base and patches environment-specific values:

```yaml
apiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1
kind: Kustomization

namespace: <environment>

resources:
  - ../../base/<app-name>

replicas:
  - name: <app-name>
    count: <replica-count>

labels:
  - pairs:
      environment: <environment>
    includeSelectors: false
```

{{- if eq (printf "%s" .Controller.Type) "argocd"}}
## 3. Create ArgoCD Application definitions

For each environment, create an Application YAML in `apps/`:

```
{{- range .Environments}}
apps/<app-name>-{{.Name}}.yaml
{{- end}}
```

Each Application points to the corresponding overlay:

```yaml
apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1
kind: Application
metadata:
  name: <app-name>-<environment>
  namespace: argocd
  finalizers:
    - resources-finalizer.argocd.argoproj.io
spec:
  project: default
  source:
    repoURL: <this-repo-url>
    targetRevision: HEAD
    path: environments/<environment>/<app-name>
  destination:
    server: https://kubernetes.default.svc
    namespace: <environment>
  syncPolicy:
    syncOptions:
      - CreateNamespace=true
```
{{- else}}
## 3. Create Flux Kustomization definitions

For each environment, create a Kustomization YAML in `apps/`:

```
{{- range .Environments}}
apps/<app-name>-{{.Name}}.yaml
{{- end}}
```

Each Kustomization points to the corresponding overlay:

```yaml
apiVersion: kustomize.toolkit.fluxcd.io/v1
kind: Kustomization
metadata:
  name: <app-name>-<environment>
  namespace: flux-system
spec:
  interval: 5m0s
  sourceRef:
    kind: GitRepository
    name: gitops-repo
    namespace: flux-system
  path: ./environments/<environment>/<app-name>
  prune: true
  targetNamespace: <environment>
```
{{- end}}

{{- end}}

## 4. Commit and push

```bash
git add -A
git commit -m "feat: onboard <app-name>"
git push
```

{{- if eq (printf "%s" .Controller.Type) "argocd"}}
The root Application in `apps/_root.yaml` will detect the new files and ArgoCD will begin syncing automatically.
{{- else}}
The root Kustomization will detect the new files and Flux will reconcile them on the next interval.
{{- end}}

## Quick checklist

{{- if eq (printf "%s" .ManifestType) "helm"}}
- [ ] Helm chart in `environments/base/<app>/`
- [ ] Values file per environment in `environments/<env>/<app>/values.yaml`
{{- if eq (printf "%s" .Controller.Type) "argocd"}}
- [ ] ArgoCD Application per environment in `apps/`
{{- else}}
- [ ] Flux HelmRelease per environment in `apps/`
{{- end}}
{{- else}}
- [ ] Base manifests in `environments/base/<app>/`
- [ ] Overlay per environment in `environments/<env>/<app>/`
{{- if eq (printf "%s" .Controller.Type) "argocd"}}
- [ ] ArgoCD Application per environment in `apps/`
{{- else}}
- [ ] Flux Kustomization per environment in `apps/`
{{- end}}
{{- end}}
- [ ] Image tag set (do not use `:latest` in staging/production)
- [ ] Resource requests and limits defined
- [ ] Health probes configured
